I am raising this suggestion as the current query doesn't return all needed results.

{noformat}
"Time to Resolution" > elapsed(24h) 
{noformat}

The query above currently doesn't return all issues as per the [documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/SERVICEDESK/Reporting+on+SLAs], "Completed SLAs or SLAs without cycles will not be returned.". I think that this query should return all issue and not only those that are current running an active SLA. We have breached() for breached issues . 

If the user doesn't want to return completed issues; then can always append another query to make sure only non-completed issues are returned; for example.

{noformat}
"TIme to Resolution" > elapsed(24h) and "Time to Resolution" != completed()
{noformat}

The query should be more flexible ( returning all results) so that it can appeal to wider use cases. If there are special conditions; users can always choose to append other queries in it to narrow down the results.

